---
title: create-instruction
description: |
  Instruct the agent to include the local instruction files `mirror-instructions.md`
  and `audit-instruction` when performing "create" or scaffolding-related tasks.
---

Purpose
-------
- Ensure the agent loads and respects the repository-level instruction artifacts
  used for mirroring `/test` into the scaffolder and for running the mirror audit.

When to use
-----------
- Trigger: user asks to "create" or "mirror" scaffolder templates, or requests an
  audit/mirroring operation for the project.

Behavior
--------
1. When the agent receives a `create-instruction` command or equivalent trigger,
   it MUST first read the following files from the repository root (in this order):
   - `mirror-instructions.md`
   - `audit-instruction`

2. After loading those files, proceed with the requested create/mirror/audit
   workflow as described by the loaded instructions.

3. If either file is missing or unreadable, the agent should stop and report
   which file is missing and how to proceed (copy file, run from correct root,
   or set permissions).

Notes
-----
- These are repository-level instructions. To use them on another device, copy
  the files into the workspace root and run the agent from the project root
  where `generate-file-structure.php` lives.
- The agent should respect the safety rules inside `mirror-instructions.md`:
  prefer small, incremental patches and stop for confirmation on ambiguous
  multi-line edits.

Files referenced
----------------
- mirror-instructions.md
- audit-instruction
